modules.description: Generates text by embedding OCaml expressions within a template, allowing dynamic content insertion through inline code blocks. It processes strings with embedded expressions, evaluating them at runtime to produce final output. Used to create dynamic HTML pages, configuration files, or any text-based output requiring runtime computation.

Escapes special HTML characters in a string, replacing '&' with `&`, '<' with `<`, '>' with `>`, '"' with `"`, and ''' with `'`. Works directly with string inputs and outputs. Used to safely render user-generated content in web interfaces.
